3x + y &= 12 \\
y &= -3x + 12 \tag{2}
\end{align*}
From equation $(2)$ we see that the $y$-intercept $b$ is equal to $12$.
The $x$-intercept $a$ can be found by setting $y$ equal to $0$ and solving for $x$:
